    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-06T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="401"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">892.51/238: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-06T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 6, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. Your 549, December 4, 2 p.m. You may assure Thai authorities that extension
                    of a credit to Thailand for current needs is fully agreed to in principle, and
                    that Department expects no delay in <pb facs="0383" n="373" xml:id="pg_373"/>
                    working out details with the appropriate lending agency of this Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
